Feature: Reparo

    Used to repair broken or damaged objects.

    Pronunciation:
        /rɛˈpɑroʊ/ re-PAR-oh
    Seen/mentioned:
        Many times throughout the books. First used by Hermione, when she uses
        it to fix a broken window. Shattered objects are often described as
        having "flown" back together. However, substances contained within
        broken objects are not restored.
    Suggested etymology: - 
    Notes:
        Harry used this spell twice to repair his wand in Harry Potter and the
        Deathly Hallows, once with a normal wand and a second time with the
        "Elder Wand" or "Wand of Destiny". Only the second attempt was
        successful.